snippet: Ms. Moran, who made it as high as No. 4 in the United States rankings, showed up at Wimbledon in 1949 wearing an unconventional short skirt with lace-trimmed underwear.
abstract: Gussie Moran, American tennis player who caused an international stir in 1949 for competing at Wimbledon in a short skirt, dies at age 89.

byline.contributor: Daniel E. Slotnik and William McDonald contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Ms. Moran, who made it as high as No. 4 in the United States rankings, showed up at Wimbledon in 1949 wearing an unconventional short skirt with lace-trimmed underwear.

headline.seo: Gussie Moran, Tennis Star, Dies at 89
headline.main: Gussie Moran, a Tennis Star Who Wore a Daring Wimbledon Outfit, Dies at 89
